Tharaka Nithi senator aspirant Francis Kiambi has said he is still in the race.He launched his campaign earlier this year, the initial hype seems to have fizzled out, raising questions on whether he has opted out. Kiambi dished out a lot of money during harambees in Tharaka constituency. Speaking at Kathwana on Sunday, he warned his rivals against disrupting his rallies. &ldquo;We should all hold peaceful campaigns. Chaos will fuel animosity,&rdquo; Kiambi said.The businessman said he will not be intimidated to drop his bid.&ldquo;They have even hatched a plot by taking my company to court to drain me financially. Even President Uhuru Kenyatta and DP William Ruto won while they were being charged at the ICC,&rdquo; Kiambi said.